{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Oatcakes","content":["Preheat oven to 190°C. Line 2 baking trays (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Place butter, water, salt and sugar into mixing bowl and heat <nobr>3 min\/90°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Add oats and bicarbonate of soda and mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>, until a crumbly dough forms.","Transfer dough onto a silicone bread mat or lightly floured work surface and shape dough with hands. Place a sheet of baking paper on top of dough and roll out thinly (2 mm). Using a cookie cutter (5 cm), cut dough into 30 rounds and place onto prepared trays.","Bake for 12-14 minutes (190°C), or until crisp. Turn off oven and allow oatcakes to cool in oven. Clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Harissa","content":["Place a ceramic or glass bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh chillies and boiling water into it. Soak chillies in boiling water (approx. 10 minutes), then drain using simmering basket and set aside.","Place cumin and coriander seeds into mixing bowl and dry roast <nobr>4 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Allow to cool for 5 minutes, then mill <nobr>3 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>.","Add garlic and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add 20 g of the oil and cook <nobr>2 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add salt, reserved chillies and remaining 20 g oil and blend <nobr>30 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Transfer into a sealable jar or container and place into refrigerator until ready to use. Clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Moroccan hommus","content":["Place garlic into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add oil and cook <nobr>1 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add  2-3 teaspoons of the reserved harissa and cook <nobr>1 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add chickpeas, water and lime juice and mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add tahini and salt and blend <nobr>10 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>, until smooth. Transfer into a serving bowl and serve with oatcakes."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Oatcakes","content":["30 g unsalted butter, cut into pieces (4-5 cm)","70 g water","½ tsp sea salt","1 tbsp raw sugar","180 g oats","¼ tsp bicarbonate of soda"]},{"title":"Harissa","content":["150 g fresh red chillies, cut into pieces","600 g boiling water","2 ½ tsp cumin seeds","2 tsp coriander seeds","5 garlic cloves","40 g extra virgin olive oil","1 tsp salt"]},{"title":"Moroccan hommus","content":["2 garlic cloves","2 tbsp extra virgin olive oil","400 g canned chickpeas, rinsed and drained (approx. 250 g after draining)","2 tbsp water","2 tbsp lime juice (approx. 1 lime)","1 tbsp tahini (see Tips)","½ tsp sea salt"]}],"id":"r102222","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-L5V1jAoLVpA\/XZMwL_-10EI\/AAAAAAAAaao\/HcAXMyBj3yIYAmWllXZJ9IovVOcBseMnwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_xvZDtvR_QZhOs7hx.png","title":"Oatcakes with Moroccan hommus","publishedAt":"2016-07-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"27.9 g","fat":"72.7 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"92.1 g","calories":"5021 kJ \/ 1195 kcal"},"usefulItems":"round cookie cutter (5 cm), baking paper, 2 baking trays (30 x 40 cm), rolling pin, silicone bread mat, ceramic or glass bowl, sealable storage jar or container, serving bowl, bowl, oven, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["To make your own tahini, refer to the recipe on this recipe chip.","To make these oatcakes suitable for those following a vegan diet, replace butter with oil of choice.","<strong><\/strong>Harissa is a spicy chilli paste from North Africa. Adjust the amount of chillies you use to suit your taste. Store harissa in a sealable jar or container in the refrigerator. Use in sauces, marinades or dips to add extra spice and flavour.","Substitute fresh chillies with dried chillies in the harissa. Soak dried chillies in water for 1 hour, then drain and use as per recipe.","<strong><\/strong>For the hommus, you can replace the lime juice with lemon juice. For a thicker consistency, replace the citrus juice with water."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","50m","6 portions"]}